<%
// Stump Grinding Service Page
%>

<!-- Page Header -->
<section class="page-header" style="background-image: url('/images/stump.jpg');">
    <div class="overlay"></div>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Stump Grinding Services in Gold Beach, OR</h1>
        <p>Professional Tree Stump Removal on the Southern Oregon Coast</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Main Content -->
<section class="service-detail section-padding">
    <div class="container">
        
        <!-- Introduction with Image -->
        <div class="service-intro">
            <div class="intro-text">
                <p>JT & Sons Tree Service LLC provides professional stump grinding services in Gold Beach, Oregon and surrounding areas including Brookings, Pistol River, Ophir, Agnes, Port Orford, Sixes, Langlois, Bandon, and Coos Bay.</p>
                <p>After a tree is removed, the remaining stump can become an unsightly obstacle and a potential safety hazard. Our stump grinding services are designed to completely remove tree stumps and restore the appearance and functionality of your landscape.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="intro-image">
                <img src="/images/stump-grinding.jpg" alt="Stump Grinding" class="rounded-image">
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Why Stump Grinding Is Important -->
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Why Stump Grinding Is Important</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Improve Property Appearance</strong> – Tree stumps can make your yard look unfinished. Removing them helps restore the clean and natural look.</li>
                <li><strong>Prevent Pest Infestations</strong> – Old stumps can attract termites, ants, beetles, and other wood-boring pests that may spread.</li>
                <li><strong>Eliminate Safety Hazards</strong> – Stumps create tripping hazards for family, visitors, and pets. Grinding them down improves safety.</li>
                <li><strong>Create Space for Landscaping</strong> – Removing a stump allows you to plant new trees, install landscaping, or expand lawn areas.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Services Include + Image Row -->
        <div class="service-include-row">
            <div class="service-list">
                <h2>Our Stump Grinding Services Include</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Tree stump grinding</li>
                    <li>Large stump removal</li>
                    <li>Multiple stump grinding</li>
                    <li>Stump grinding after tree removal</li>
                    <li>Surface root grinding</li>
                    <li>Residential and commercial stump removal</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="service-image">
                <img src="/images/di.jpeg" alt="Stump Grinding Process" class="rounded-image">
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Process -->
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Our Stump Grinding Process</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Stump Inspection</strong> – We inspect the stump and surrounding area to determine the safest and most effective grinding approach.</li>
                <li><strong>Professional Stump Grinding</strong> – Using specialized equipment, we grind the stump below ground level so the area can be restored.</li>
                <li><strong>Debris Removal</strong> – Wood chips and debris are cleared from the area to leave your property neat and tidy.</li>
                <li><strong>Site Restoration</strong> – The area can be leveled and prepared for grass, landscaping, or new planting.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact Info Box -->
        <div class="contact-info-box">
            <h3>Get a Free Stump Grinding Estimate</h3>
            <p>
                <i class="fas fa-phone-alt"></i> Office: <a href="tel:<%= sitePhone %>"><%= sitePhone %></a><br>
                <i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i> Cell/Text: <a href="tel:<%= siteCell %>"><%= siteCell %></a><br>
                <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Email: <a href="mailto:<%= siteEmail %>"><%= siteEmail %></a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>